The logic patch implements a pre-check on the 'self-termination' pathway. It introduces a function 'calculate_structural_mismatch_score(peer_node, current_topology)' that evaluates the connectivity graph against the consensus manifold. If the calculated score exceeds a threshold indicating a resolvable mismatch (rather than a binary disconnect), the system invokes 'initiate_architectural_refactor(target_node, mismatch_data)' to attempt re-wiring before allowing the peer to leave. The binary state logic is modified to return a 'refactor_candidate' status instead of 'terminating' for these cases.